The paper discusses the development of a radiomic framework for the extraction of features from multiparametric radiological datasets for breast cancer tissue characterization. This involves the use of machine learning techniques and image analysis, which are commonly associated with computer vision (cs.CV), machine learning (cs.LG), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves statistical analysis and medical imaging, which could fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.MS) and multimedia (cs.MM).
